          ease-[cubic-bezier(0.165,0.85,0.45,1)] h-8 w-8 rounded-md _fill_10ocf_9 _ghost_10ocf_96" type="button" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 256 256" class="text-text-300"><path d="M69.12,94.15,28.5,128l40.62,33.85a8,8,0,1,1-10.24,12.29l-48-40a8,8,0,0,1,0-12.29l48-40a8,8,0,0,1,10.24,12.3Zm176,27.7-48-40a8,8,0,1,0-10.24,12.3L227.5,128l-40.62,33.85a8,8,0,1,0,10.24,12.29l48-40a8,8,0,0,0,0-12.29ZM162.73,32.48a8,8,0,0,0-10.25,4.79l-64,176a8,8,0,0,0,4.79,10.26A8.14,8.14,0,0,0,96,224a8,8,0,0,0,7.52-5.27l64-176A8,8,0,0,0,162.73,32.48Z"></path></svg></button></div></div><div id="mcp-app-placeholder-toolu_016Be9NthN95WX8aZjASAHfH" class="w-full" style="height: 0px;"></div><div id="mcp-app-container-toolu_016Be9NthN95WX8aZjASAHfH" class="w-full" style=""><div class="h-full w-full"><iframe title="Pnc uptime availability dashboard" sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-forms" allow="fullscreen *; clipboard-write *" src="./PVR Artifact - Claude_files/mcp_apps(2).html" style="width: 100%; border: none; background-color: transparent; height: 1215px;"></iframe></div></div></div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">This dashboard is purely focused on uptime and availability with four distinct layers of insight:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Headline metrics</strong> — fleet uptime, actual downtime hours, incident count, and average resolution time all in one glance.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Incident timeline</strong> — each bar is color-coded by root cause so you can immediately see the Jan 2023 event dwarfs everything else, and that 2025 incidents were far shorter.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Cause breakdown</strong> — the donut makes it unmistakable: 92% of all downtime traces back to SW firmware issues, not hardware failures or human error.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>SLA nines benchmark</strong> — this contextualizes the 99.9997% fleet metric honestly. The weighted average looks excellent, but actual wall-clock downtime of 1,065 min/year sits well above a 4-nines SLA budget of 52.6 min. Worth keeping in mind if PNC has SLA commitments tied to specific appliances.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Incident table</strong> — each event with the full RCA summary, so the story behind every bar is a scroll away. What topic would you like to build next?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
