<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The logarithmic bar chart puts everything in one glance — the key insight being that PNC's bar is taller than the 3-nines reference bar, which immediately tells the story without needing to do the math. A linear scale would have made the lower tiers invisible.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The summary cards below the chart give the exact minutes and hours side-by-side so you can see PNC sandwiched between 3 and 4 nines at a glance.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The budget consumed section at the bottom reframes each incident individually against the 4-nines budget — so you can see that even removing the massive Jan 2023 event, three of the remaining four incidents would each independently bust a 4-nines annual allowance on their own. Only the April 2025 event (15 min) would have been "safe."</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
