          ease-[cubic-bezier(0.165,0.85,0.45,1)] h-8 w-8 rounded-md _fill_10ocf_9 _ghost_10ocf_96" type="button" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 256 256" class="text-text-300"><path d="M69.12,94.15,28.5,128l40.62,33.85a8,8,0,1,1-10.24,12.29l-48-40a8,8,0,0,1,0-12.29l48-40a8,8,0,0,1,10.24,12.3Zm176,27.7-48-40a8,8,0,1,0-10.24,12.3L227.5,128l-40.62,33.85a8,8,0,1,0,10.24,12.29l48-40a8,8,0,0,0,0-12.29ZM162.73,32.48a8,8,0,0,0-10.25,4.79l-64,176a8,8,0,0,0,4.79,10.26A8.14,8.14,0,0,0,96,224a8,8,0,0,0,7.52-5.27l64-176A8,8,0,0,0,162.73,32.48Z"></path></svg></button></div></div><div id="mcp-app-placeholder-toolu_01396kjcQn4PyjjSBtDweMv6" class="w-full" style="height: 0px;"></div><div id="mcp-app-container-toolu_01396kjcQn4PyjjSBtDweMv6" class="w-full" style=""><div class="h-full w-full"><iframe title="Pnc data security dashboard" sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-forms" allow="fullscreen *; clipboard-write *" src="./PVR Artifact - Claude_files/mcp_apps(4).html" style="width: 100%; border: none; background-color: transparent; height: 1323px;"></iframe></div></div></div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The dashboard is organized into six focused sections:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Top metrics</strong> — four headline numbers that surface the two critical risks immediately: SafeMode and contract expiry.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>SafeMode</strong> — side-by-side FA vs FB panels showing 100% of the fleet is either disabled or unreported. This is the single biggest security exposure — with SafeMode off, ransomware can permanently delete snapshots with no recovery path.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Subscription types</strong> — bar breakdown distinguishing Evergreen//Forever (perpetual, no renewal risk) from Evergreen//Foundation (term-based, needs contract) and 19 with unknown status.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Contract risk</strong> — the bar chart makes the July 2026 cliff unmissable. 71 appliances expire in the same month, meaning a single missed renewal conversation puts 56% of the fleet without security patch eligibility simultaneously.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Firmware posture</strong> — FA and FB separated, each version scored by currency. FlashBlade is largely healthy; FlashArray is where the exposure sits with 86 arrays on 6.5.9.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Telemetry</strong> — 100% coverage is a green, but the 8-day lag is flagged as a real blind spot for real-time incident detection.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Risk summary row</strong> at the bottom gives a single-glance scorecard across all five dimensions with consistent traffic-light scoring.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
