          ease-[cubic-bezier(0.165,0.85,0.45,1)] h-8 w-8 rounded-md _fill_10ocf_9 _ghost_10ocf_96" type="button" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 256 256" class="text-text-300"><path d="M69.12,94.15,28.5,128l40.62,33.85a8,8,0,1,1-10.24,12.29l-48-40a8,8,0,0,1,0-12.29l48-40a8,8,0,0,1,10.24,12.3Zm176,27.7-48-40a8,8,0,1,0-10.24,12.3L227.5,128l-40.62,33.85a8,8,0,1,0,10.24,12.29l48-40a8,8,0,0,0,0-12.29ZM162.73,32.48a8,8,0,0,0-10.25,4.79l-64,176a8,8,0,0,0,4.79,10.26A8.14,8.14,0,0,0,96,224a8,8,0,0,0,7.52-5.27l64-176A8,8,0,0,0,162.73,32.48Z"></path></svg></button></div></div><div id="mcp-app-placeholder-toolu_019PjKtpNZ4URAeL76Km1T2T" class="w-full" style="height: 0px;"></div><div id="mcp-app-container-toolu_019PjKtpNZ4URAeL76Km1T2T" class="w-full" style=""><div class="h-full w-full"><iframe title="Pnc esg dashboard" sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-forms" allow="fullscreen *; clipboard-write *" src="./PVR Artifact - Claude_files/mcp_apps(5).html" style="width: 100%; border: none; background-color: transparent; height: 1286px;"></iframe></div></div></div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The entire dashboard is wrapped in a green theme with nature-inspired illustrations throughout. Here's what each section tells:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Impact equivalents</strong> — the four illustrated rows (trees, cars, racks, hard drives) translate abstract energy numbers into tangible real-world comparisons. 286,570 trees or 1,371 fewer cars on the road land much better in an executive ESG conversation than raw kWh figures.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Energy efficiency vs. industry</strong> — the side-by-side bar makes the 88.7% power reduction instantly visible. Traditional SAN would draw 2,994 kW vs. PNC's actual 339 kW.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Trends</strong> — the reduction ratio is declining (3.08x → 2.65x, down 14%) which is worth watching — it could mean more compressible data is being displaced by already-compressed workloads. Utilization is gently climbing, which is a green positive.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Capacity stack</strong> — shows the full story of physical used, headroom, and the bonus capacity unlocked by dedup/compression in a single bar.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Opportunity callout</strong> at the bottom is the forward-looking ESG action item: consolidating the 52 under-utilized arrays could save another ~347 tonnes of CO₂/year without buying anything new.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
