          ease-[cubic-bezier(0.165,0.85,0.45,1)] h-8 w-8 rounded-md _fill_10ocf_9 _ghost_10ocf_96" type="button" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 256 256" class="text-text-300"><path d="M69.12,94.15,28.5,128l40.62,33.85a8,8,0,1,1-10.24,12.29l-48-40a8,8,0,0,1,0-12.29l48-40a8,8,0,0,1,10.24,12.3Zm176,27.7-48-40a8,8,0,1,0-10.24,12.3L227.5,128l-40.62,33.85a8,8,0,1,0,10.24,12.29l48-40a8,8,0,0,0,0-12.29ZM162.73,32.48a8,8,0,0,0-10.25,4.79l-64,176a8,8,0,0,0,4.79,10.26A8.14,8.14,0,0,0,96,224a8,8,0,0,0,7.52-5.27l64-176A8,8,0,0,0,162.73,32.48Z"></path></svg></button></div></div><div id="mcp-app-placeholder-toolu_01FhkvPMyj8771Ld21yTn6Ea" class="w-full" style="height: 0px;"></div><div id="mcp-app-container-toolu_01FhkvPMyj8771Ld21yTn6Ea" class="w-full" style=""><div class="h-full w-full"><iframe title="Pnc support cases dashboard" sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-forms" allow="fullscreen *; clipboard-write *" src="./PVR Artifact - Claude_files/mcp_apps(6).html" style="width: 100%; border: none; background-color: transparent; height: 1905px;"></iframe></div></div></div><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Here's how the dashboard tells the full story across its sections:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Headline row</strong> — the four metrics immediately establish the health posture: 2,019 cases total, 80.6% proactive, 99.5% resolved, 10 open right now.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Monthly trend</strong> — the stacked bars across 27 months reveal the most important signal: the Jan 2026 reactive spike (46 reactive vs. 24 proactive) is the worst month on record and worth a direct conversation. 2024 showed a very healthy proactive-dominant pattern that has eroded into 2026.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Proactive rate by year</strong> — the horizontal bars make the declining trend impossible to miss: from 87% in 2023–2024 down to 40% YTD in 2026. This is the key talking point for a business review.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Severity breakdown</strong> — the four metric cards combine count, share, and proactive rate per tier. The standout: 100% of all 40 Sev-1 cases were proactively detected, never customer-reported. That's a strong story.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Category chart</strong> — Software is where reactive cases concentrate (234 reactive vs. 334 proactive). Hardware and Environmentals are almost entirely proactive — those are caught by monitoring, not customers.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Resolution time</strong> — horizontal stacked bars show Sev-4 has the worst long-tail (61 cases &gt;4 weeks), which is counterintuitive but explained by lower urgency deferral. Proactive cases close 32% faster than reactive ones.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Open cases table</strong> — sorted by age, with Pro/React badges so you immediately see which open cases are customer-driven pain vs. monitored issues awaiting action.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
