<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Everpure theming applied throughout</strong> — the warm <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem] inline-flex items-center h-5"><span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 border-[0.5px] border-border-200 rounded flex-shrink-0 shadow-sm mr-1 align-middle" style="background-color: rgb(255, 245, 227);"></span>#fff5e3</code> background, <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem] inline-flex items-center h-5"><span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 border-[0.5px] border-border-200 rounded flex-shrink-0 shadow-sm mr-1 align-middle" style="background-color: rgb(239, 237, 232);"></span>#efede8</code> surface for the toggle pill and insight cards, Pure Orange (<code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem] inline-flex items-center h-5"><span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 border-[0.5px] border-border-200 rounded flex-shrink-0 shadow-sm mr-1 align-middle" style="background-color: rgb(255, 112, 35);"></span>#ff7023</code>) as the active state and primary chart accent, Basil (<code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem] inline-flex items-center h-5"><span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 border-[0.5px] border-border-200 rounded flex-shrink-0 shadow-sm mr-1 align-middle" style="background-color: rgb(90, 99, 89);"></span>#5a6359</code>) and Storage Stone (<code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem] inline-flex items-center h-5"><span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 border-[0.5px] border-border-200 rounded flex-shrink-0 shadow-sm mr-1 align-middle" style="background-color: rgb(208, 200, 186);"></span>#d0c8ba</code>) as secondary chart colors, and the pink destructive (<code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem] inline-flex items-center h-5"><span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 border-[0.5px] border-border-200 rounded flex-shrink-0 shadow-sm mr-1 align-middle" style="background-color: rgb(218, 77, 114);"></span>#da4d72</code>) for the anomaly callout.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Toggle control</strong> — the pill-style switcher uses the Everpure input pattern with a smooth <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">background</code> + <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">box-shadow</code> transition on the active state. No page reload, just a CSS <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">visible</code> class swap with a subtle <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">fadeIn</code> animation so the chart entrance feels intentional.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>DM Sans + DM Mono</strong> — replacing the generic system font to give the numbers a more refined, distinctive feel consistent with the skill's guidance to avoid generic font choices.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Insight cards</strong> — the three callout cards below each chart update with context-relevant numbers per view, so you're never reading stale information when you toggle. The Sev-1 anomaly card on the FRT view uses the pink destructive surface to visually flag it as an outlier without hiding it.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
